This paper focuses on robotic grasping using deep learning and large-scale data collection. The paper discusses training a convolutional neural network to predict the probability of successful grasps using monocular camera images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses real-time control of the gripper, which falls under robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning for hand-eye coordination, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
